Operculum (
Figs. 20–21
) dark brown, ovate with apical nucleus in center and numerous concentric ridges. Attached surface with five or six growth lines and broad callused rim.

Radula (
Figs. 24–27
) rachiglossate with a rachidian tooth bearing a long, narrow, central cusp, a narrow, short, lateral denticle on the inner side of the shorter lateral cusp and several outer lateral denticles between the lateral and the low, fairly broad, marginal cusps. Central cusp longest. Lateral cusps splayed outwards. Lateral teeth sickle-shaped with long, narrow cusp and broad base.

Preserved animal (
Fig. 29
) is pale yellowish in color, tentacles are mid sized with sub-terminal black eyes of moderate size. The penis is broad and muscular, extends half the length of the mantle cavity and has a terminal papilla.
